{"questionId":"3859145","questionHtml":"<p>A car accelerates uniformly. The car passes point X at time <em>t</em><sub>1</sub> with velocity <em>v</em><sub>1</sub> and point Y at time <em>t</em><sub>2</sub> with velocity <em>v</em><sub>2</sub>. The distance XY is <em>s</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f3b07f8b01b7eed3c72cdfa0d2d5b5dda20e312f.png\"></p>\n<p>The following expressions are proposed for the magnitude of its acceleration <em>a</em>:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">I. &nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></mrow><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">II. &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\">III.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>Which is correct?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; I and II only</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; I and III only</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; II and III only</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; I, II and III</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3859145","referenceCode":"23M.1A.SL.TZ1.4","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A car accelerates uniformly. The car passes point X at time t1 with velocity v1 and point Y at time t2 with velocity v2. The distance XY is s. The following expressions are propose","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.1 Kinematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}